  <div class="formula">
    <div class="formula-top"><span class="formula-name">Cosine Similarity — The Gold Standard for Text</span><span class="formula-badge">Always use for NLP</span></div>
    <div class="formula-eq">cos(θ) = (A · B) / (|A| × |B|) &nbsp;→&nbsp; range: −1 to +1 (higher = more similar)</div>
    <div class="formula-desc">Two embedding vectors that mean the same thing will point in nearly the same direction in high-dimensional space — cos(θ) ≈ 1. Unrelated meanings → cos(θ) ≈ 0. Opposite meanings → cos(θ) ≈ −1.</div>
    <div class="formula-note"><strong style="color:var(--gold)">Famous Word2Vec magic:</strong> king − man + woman ≈ queen · This works because vector arithmetic corresponds to semantic arithmetic in embedding space.</div>
