  <div class="g3">
    <div class="card card-rose">
      <div class="card-title ct-rose">Hallucination — The Core Problem</div>
      <p>LLMs predict the <em>most statistically likely next token</em> — not the most factually correct one. They can confidently state false information.</p>
      <p><strong>Mitigation:</strong> RAG (retrieval from facts), temperature=0, verification chains, grounding.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-cyan">
      <div class="card-title ct-cyan">Context Window</div>
      <p>The maximum number of tokens the model can "see" at once. GPT-4: 128K. Claude: 200K. Gemini 1.5: 1M. Everything outside the window is forgotten.</p>
      <p>Longer context = higher memory cost (quadratic attention).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-violet">
      <div class="card-title ct-violet">Quantization</div>
      <p>Reduce model weight precision: FP32 (4 bytes) → FP16 (2 bytes) → INT8 (1 byte) → INT4 (0.5 bytes). 4-bit quantization = 8× smaller model with ~5% quality loss.</p>
      <p><strong>GGUF / GGML:</strong> Ollama format for local inference.</p>
    </div>
