      <p>Provide 2-5 examples of the task in the prompt. Dramatically improves performance on novel tasks.</p>
      <div class="code" style="font-size:11.5px"><span class="str">"positive: 'I love it!'
negative: 'I hate it.'
Classify: 'It is okay.'"</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="g2">
    <div class="card card-violet">
      <div class="card-title ct-violet">Chain-of-Thought (CoT)</div>
      <p>Tell the model to "think step by step". This unlocks reasoning capabilities on complex problems. Adding "Let's think step by step" to a prompt increased GPT accuracy on math from 17% to 78%.</p>
      <div class="code" style="font-size:11.5px"><span class="str">"Solve this math problem.
Think step by step.
Q: If 5 workers paint 5 walls..."</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-rose">
      <div class="card-title ct-rose">ReAct Prompting</div>
      <p>Combines <strong>Re</strong>asoning + <strong>Act</strong>ion. The model reasons about what to do, then takes an action (tool call), observes the result, reasons again. Foundation of AI Agents.</p>
      <div class="code" style="font-size:11.5px"><span class="cm"># Thought → Action → Observation loop</span>
<span class="str">Thought: I need to search for X
Action: search("X")
Observation: [result]
Thought: Based on this...</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card card-lime">
    <div class="card-title ct-lime">Structured Prompting Best Practices</div>
    <div class="code"><span class="cm"># Production-grade system prompt structure</span>
<span class="str">"""
ROLE: You are an expert [domain] assistant.

