</div>
<div class="phase-title">RAG — Retrieval-Augmented Generation</div>
<p class="phase-desc" style="margin-bottom:40px">Enterprise architecture for grounding LLMs in private, up-to-date knowledge</p>

<section class="section" id="rag-core">
  <div class="section-head">
    <div class="sec-icon si-gold">🔍</div>
    <div class="sec-meta">
      <div class="sec-tag">Chapter 7 — Enterprise Deep Dive</div>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Complete RAG Architecture</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout c-gold">
    <div class="c-icon">💡</div>
    <div class="c-body">
      <strong>Why RAG?</strong>
      LLMs have a training cutoff and no access to private company data. Fine-tuning is expensive. RAG gives LLMs access to any document, in real-time, without retraining. Used in every enterprise AI deployment.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flow">
    <div style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--text3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:12px;text-align:center">RAG Pipeline — Ingestion (Write Path)</div>
    <div class="flow-row">
      <div class="flow-box active"><div class="flow-label">Documents</div><div class="flow-text">PDF, DOCX, URLs</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box"><div class="flow-label">Chunking</div><div class="flow-text">Split into segments</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box"><div class="flow-label">Embed</div><div class="flow-text">Vector per chunk</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box"><div class="flow-label">Index + Store</div><div class="flow-text">Vector DB + Metadata</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-arrow" style="margin:20px 0 12px">↕</div>
    <div style="font-family:var(--fm);font-size:10px;color:var(--text3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:12px;text-align:center">RAG Pipeline — Query (Read Path)</div>
    <div class="flow-row">
      <div class="flow-box active"><div class="flow-label">User Query</div><div class="flow-text">"What is our refund policy?"</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box"><div class="flow-label">Embed Query</div><div class="flow-text">Same model</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box highlight"><div class="flow-label">ANN Search</div><div class="flow-text">Top-K chunks</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box"><div class="flow-label">Rerank</div><div class="flow-text">Cross-encoder</div></div>
      <div class="flow-row-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-box violet"><div class="flow-label">LLM + Context</div><div class="flow-text">Generate Answer</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tw" style="margin-top:20px">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Chunking Strategy</th><th>Method</th><th>Best For</th><th>Risk</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="hl">Fixed-Size</td><td>Split every N characters</td><td>Simple text, quick start</td><td>Breaks sentences mid-thought</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="hl">Sentence-based</td><td>Split by sentence/paragraph boundaries</td><td>General documents</td><td>Variable chunk size</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="hl" style="color:var(--gold)">Semantic ★</td><td>Split when topic changes (cosine similarity drop)</td><td>Complex multi-topic docs</td><td>Requires embedding at chunk time</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="hl">Hierarchical</td><td>Parent chunks + child chunks</td><td>Legal, financial, tech docs</td><td>Complex to implement</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="hl">Sliding Window</td><td>Overlap N tokens between chunks</td><td>Preventing context loss at boundaries</td><td>Duplicate content in index</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="g2">
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <div class="card-title ct-gold">Hybrid Search in RAG</div>
      <p>Pure semantic search misses exact keyword matches. Hybrid search combines:</p>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Dense retrieval</strong> — semantic similarity (embeddings)</li>
        <li><strong>Sparse retrieval</strong> — BM25 keyword matching</li>
        <li><strong>RRF fusion</strong> — merge both ranked lists</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Weaviate, Qdrant, Milvus all support native hybrid search.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-cyan">
      <div class="card-title ct-cyan">Reranking</div>
      <p>After retrieving Top-20 chunks, use a <strong>cross-encoder reranker</strong> to re-score each chunk against the query more accurately (cross-encoder looks at query + chunk together, not independently).</p>
      <p>Example: <code style="font-family:var(--fm);color:var(--gold)">cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2</code></p>
      <p>Retrieve 20 → Rerank → Pass Top-5 to LLM</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="g2">
    <div class="card card-violet">
      <div class="card-title ct-violet">Graph RAG</div>
      <p>Traditional RAG retrieves isolated chunks. <strong>Graph RAG</strong> builds a knowledge graph from documents — entities (people, places, concepts) connected by relationships.</p>
      <p>Queries can traverse graph relationships: <em>"How does protein X relate to disease Y through pathway Z?"</em> — impossible with chunk-only RAG.</p>
      <p>Used for: medical research, legal discovery, supply chain analysis.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-rose">
      <div class="card-title ct-rose">Agentic RAG</div>
      <p>An AI agent dynamically decides how to retrieve information:</p>
      <ul class="bl rose" style="font-size:12.5px">
        <li>Decompose complex queries into sub-queries</li>
        <li>Iteratively retrieve → read → decide what else to retrieve</li>
        <li>Use tools: web search, APIs, multiple vector stores</li>
        <li>Self-correct if retrieved info is insufficient</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="code">
<span class="cm"># Production RAG with LangChain — Complete Pipeline</span>
<span class="kw">from</span> langchain.document_loaders <span class="kw">import</span> PyPDFLoader
<span class="kw">from</span> langchain.text_splitter <span class="kw">import</span> RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter
<span class="kw">from</span> langchain_community.vectorstores <span class="kw">import</span> Milvus
<span class="kw">from</span> langchain_ibm <span class="kw">import</span> WatsonxEmbeddings, WatsonxLLM
<span class="kw">from</span> langchain.chains <span class="kw">import</span> RetrievalQA

<span class="cm"># 1. Load documents</span>
loader = <span class="fn">PyPDFLoader</span>(<span class="str">"company_docs.pdf"</span>)
docs = loader.<span class="fn">load</span>()

<span class="cm"># 2. Chunk</span>
splitter = <span class="fn">RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter</span>(
    chunk_size=<span class="num">512</span>, chunk_overlap=<span class="num">64</span>
)
chunks = splitter.<span class="fn">split_documents</span>(docs)

<span class="cm"># 3. Embed + Store (IBM watsonx + Milvus)</span>
embeddings = <span class="fn">WatsonxEmbeddings</span>(model_id=<span class="str">"ibm/slate-125m-english-rtrvr-v2"</span>)
vectorstore = Milvus.<span class="fn">from_documents</span>(chunks, embeddings,
    collection_name=<span class="str">"enterprise_kb"</span>)

<span class="cm"># 4. RAG Chain</span>
llm = <span class="fn">WatsonxLLM</span>(model_id=<span class="str">"meta-llama/llama-3-3-70b-instruct"</span>)
qa_chain = RetrievalQA.<span class="fn">from_chain_type</span>(
    llm=llm,
    retriever=vectorstore.<span class="fn">as_retriever</span>(search_kwargs={<span class="str">"k"</span>: <span class="num">5</span>})
)

result = qa_chain.<span class="fn">invoke</span>({<span class="str">"query"</span>: <span class="str">"What is our refund policy?"</span>})</div>
</section>

