<section class="section" id="adv-llm">
  <div class="section-head">
    <div class="sec-icon si-violet">⚙️</div>
    <div class="sec-meta">
      <div class="sec-tag">Chapter 10</div>
      <h2 class="sec-title">PEFT, LoRA, RLHF & Inference Optimization</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card card-violet">
    <div class="card-title ct-violet">LoRA — Low-Rank Adaptation (Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning)</div>
    <p>Full fine-tuning LLaMA-3-70B requires ~280GB of GPU memory. LoRA freezes original weights and adds tiny trainable matrices (rank decomposition) alongside attention layers. Only 0.1–1% of parameters are trained.</p>
    <div class="code"><span class="cm"># LoRA: Instead of training W (7B params), train A×B where r << d</span>
<span class="cm"># W_new = W_frozen + (A × B) × scaling</span>
<span class="cm"># A: d×r matrix,  B: r×d matrix,  r: rank (typically 8-64)</span>

<span class="kw">from</span> peft <span class="kw">import</span> LoraConfig, get_peft_model, TaskType

config = <span class="fn">LoraConfig</span>(
    task_type=TaskType.CAUSAL_LM,
    r=<span class="num">16</span>,              <span class="cm"># rank (higher = more capacity)</span>
    lora_alpha=<span class="num">32</span>,     <span class="cm"># scaling factor</span>
    lora_dropout=<span class="num">0.1</span>,
    target_modules=[<span class="str">"q_proj"</span>, <span class="str">"v_proj"</span>]  <span class="cm"># which layers to adapt</span>
)
model = <span class="fn">get_peft_model</span>(base_model, config)
model.<span class="fn">print_trainable_parameters</span>()
<span class="cm"># trainable params: 4,194,304 || all params: 6,738,415,616 || 0.062%</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="g2">
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <div class="card-title ct-gold">QLoRA — Quantized LoRA</div>
      <p>Combines 4-bit quantization of base model + LoRA adapters. Enables fine-tuning 70B models on a single 48GB GPU (vs multiple A100s for full fine-tuning).</p>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>4-bit NF4:</strong> Optimal 4-bit quantization for normally distributed weights</li>
        <li><strong>Double quantization:</strong> Quantize the quantization constants too</li>
        <li><strong>Paged optimizers:</strong> Handle memory spikes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-cyan">
      <div class="card-title ct-cyan">RLHF — Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback</div>
      <p>How ChatGPT was made helpful. Three stages:</p>
      <ol style="margin-left:16px;color:var(--text2);font-size:13px;line-height:1.9">
        <li>SFT: Supervised fine-tune on demonstration data</li>
        <li>Reward Model: Humans rank outputs, train RM</li>
        <li>PPO: RL fine-tune LLM to maximize reward</li>
      </ol>
      <p>DPO (Direct Preference Optimization) is simpler alternative — no separate RM needed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

