  <div class="g2">
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <div class="card-title ct-gold">Mixture of Experts (MoE)</div>
      <p>Instead of activating all model parameters for every token, MoE selects only a subset of "expert" sub-networks (FFN layers) for each token using a learned <strong>router</strong>.</p>
      <p>Mixtral 8×7B: 8 experts per layer, activates 2 per token. Total 47B params but only 13B active — speed of small model, quality of large model.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-violet">
      <div class="card-title ct-violet">Diffusion Models</div>
      <p>Learn to <strong>reverse a noising process</strong>. Start with pure Gaussian noise. Iteratively denoise, guided by a text prompt (via cross-attention to CLIP embeddings).</p>
      <p>Stable Diffusion, DALL-E 3, Midjourney. <strong>Latent diffusion</strong> operates in compressed latent space (faster + cheaper than pixel space).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="g3">
    <div class="card card-rose">
      <div class="card-title ct-rose">Constitutional AI</div>
      <p>Anthropic's method for training AI to be helpful, harmless, and honest. The model critiques and revises its own outputs based on a set of principles (constitution) — without human labelers rating every output.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-cyan">
      <div class="card-title ct-cyan">Long-Context Systems</div>
      <p>Challenges beyond 128K tokens: attention is O(n²) quadratic in context length. Solutions: <strong>Ring Attention</strong> (distributed), <strong>Flash Attention</strong> (memory-efficient), <strong>ALiBi</strong> (length generalization), <strong>RoPE</strong> positional embeddings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-lime">
      <div class="card-title ct-lime">AI Safety</div>
      <p>Alignment research ensures AI systems pursue intended goals. Techniques: RLHF, DPO, Constitutional AI, red-teaming, interpretability (understanding what's happening inside models). Critical as AI becomes more capable.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

