  <div class="gloss-grid">
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Attention Mechanism</div><div class="gloss-def">Mechanism allowing each token to weigh the importance of all other tokens when building its representation</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Autoregressive</div><div class="gloss-def">Generating one token at a time, each conditioned on all previously generated tokens</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">BPE</div><div class="gloss-def">Byte-Pair Encoding — tokenization method that merges frequent character pairs iteratively</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Constitutional AI</div><div class="gloss-def">Anthropic's method of training AI to follow a set of principles using self-critique and revision</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Context Window</div><div class="gloss-def">Maximum number of tokens an LLM can process in a single forward pass</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Cross-Entropy Loss</div><div class="gloss-def">Standard loss function for classification — measures divergence between predicted and true distributions</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Embedding</div><div class="gloss-def">Dense vector representation of data (text, image, etc.) encoding semantic meaning</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Flash Attention</div><div class="gloss-def">Memory-efficient attention implementation that avoids materializing the full attention matrix</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">GELU</div><div class="gloss-def">Gaussian Error Linear Unit — smooth activation function used in transformers (GPT, BERT)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Hallucination</div><div class="gloss-def">LLM generating factually incorrect but confident-sounding information</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">KV Cache</div><div class="gloss-def">Cached Key-Value matrices from previous tokens to avoid recomputation during inference</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">LoRA</div><div class="gloss-def">Low-Rank Adaptation — PEFT method adding trainable low-rank matrices to frozen model weights</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">MoE</div><div class="gloss-def">Mixture of Experts — architecture activating only a subset of "expert" FFN layers per token</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Perplexity</div><div class="gloss-def">Measure of how well an LLM predicts a text sample — lower = better language model</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">PEFT</div><div class="gloss-def">Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning — methods that train only a small fraction of model parameters</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Positional Encoding</div><div class="gloss-def">Vectors added to token embeddings to provide position/order information to attention</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">RAG</div><div class="gloss-def">Retrieval-Augmented Generation — augmenting LLM context with retrieved relevant documents</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">ReAct</div><div class="gloss-def">Reasoning + Acting — prompt pattern for AI agents combining chain-of-thought with tool use</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">RLHF</div><div class="gloss-def">Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback — aligning LLMs with human preferences</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Scaling Laws</div><div class="gloss-def">Empirical observation that model performance scales predictably with model size, data, and compute</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Temperature</div><div class="gloss-def">Sampling parameter controlling randomness of LLM output (0=greedy, >1=more random)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Token</div><div class="gloss-def">Smallest unit of text an LLM processes — roughly 0.75 words; GPT-4 uses ~100K token vocab</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">vLLM</div><div class="gloss-def">High-throughput LLM serving library using PagedAttention for efficient KV cache management</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Vanishing Gradient</div><div class="gloss-def">Training problem where gradients shrink exponentially in deep/recurrent networks</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

